column2: ('Useful data type built into Python indexed by keys which can be any immutable type. Strings and numbers can always be keys.',  'https://docs.python.org/2/tutorial/datastructures.html')
('The so-called CSV (Comma Separated Values) format is the most common import and export format for spreadsheets and databases.' , 'https://docs.python.org/3/library/csv.html')
('A named entity in a function (or method) definition that specifies an argument that the function can accept.',  'https://docs.python.org/2/glossary.html')

('A Linux console terminal is one of the system consoles provided in the Linux kernel.The Linux console terminal acts as the medium for input and output operations for a Linux system.',  'https://www.techopedia.com/definition/26897/linux-console-terminal')
('A data type having two values (usually denoted true and false) intended to represent the truth values of logic and Boolean algebra.',  'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boolean_data_type')

('A class is an extensible program-code-template for creating objects providing initial values for state (member variables) and implementations of behavior (member functions or methods).',  'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Class_(computer_programming)')
('A function is a block of organized reusable code that is used to perform a single related action.', 'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/python/python_functions.htm')
('A module is a file containing Python definitions and statements. The file name is the module name with the suffix .py appended.',  'https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/modules.html')
('A variable is a location in memory used to store some data (value).',  'https://www.programiz.com/python-programming/variables-datatypes')
('Sequence of statements which is specified once but which may be carried out several times in succession.',  'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Control_flow#Loops')

('ASCII character table includes descriptions of the first 32 non-printing characters. ASCII was actually designed for use with teletypes and so the descriptions are somewhat obscure.',  'http://www.asciitable.com')
('A tuple is a sequence of immutable Python objects.',  'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/python/python_tuples.htm')

('The list is a most versatile datatype available in Python which can be written as a list of comma-separated values (items) between square brackets.',  'https://www.tutorialspoint.com/python/python_lists.htm')
('A value passed to a function (or method) when calling the function.',  'https://docs.python.org/3.3/glossary.html')
